In FY 2025, MCM USV will continue mine neutralization payload requirements definition The government awarded a three-year Software Support Activity (SSA) and
Payload Integration Contract in FY 2025 and a five-year IDIQ for in service engineering support. The government awarded a prototype for a Multi-Mission Unmanned
Surface Vehicle (MMUSV) to explore as an option for a lower cost, more producible variant of the MCM USV.

In FY 2026, the program will start Mine Neutralization Engineering Design Model design, fabrication and integration onto the craft. Additionally, the program will start the
integration of AN/AQS-24C MH Sonar PDS and payload onto the MCM USV, planning to meet MCM MP FOC in FY31. AN/AQS-24C sonar integration can potentially fill
the gap of MCM MPs for MH capability in FY28 and FY29 and is a risk mitigation to meet MCM MP FOC in FY31 and improved Force Generation. Finally, the program
continues to explore MMUSV as a lower-cost, more producible alternative to MCM USV.

In FY 2027, the program will continue integration of the Mine Neutralization and AN/AQS-24C into the MCM USV, complete design upgrades to address obsolescence
and to improve craft design based on fleet feedback and address future payload integration efforts in support of force generation, and continue development and
integration of the MMUSV.




