INSERT INTO public.pe_narratives (pe_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, accomplishments, planned_program, performance_metrics, other_program_funding, raw_text, content_hash, section_hashes, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$0603506N$$, 2027, $$The Surface Ship Torpedo Defense (SSTD) program provides a detect-to-engage layered torpedo defense capability. The four (4) major efforts that comprise SSTD are
the AN/SLQ-25 (NIXIE) system, Torpedo Warning System (TWS), the Countermeasure Anti-Torpedo (CAT), and Acoustic Device Countermeasure (Surface ADC MK2).
A layered torpedo defense to protect surface ships against current and future threats. SSTD development will include a new anti-torpedo Hard Kill (HK) capability by
pairing proven technology and the MK 58 the Compact Rapid Attack Weapon (CRAW) with improved AN/SLQ-25E that has additional software capabilities. An upgrade
to the AN/SLQ25E system using MK 58 CRAW along with an Acoustic Device Countermeasure (ADC) launcher is detailed below as the NIXIE HK.

 FY 2027 funding will support the continued development of the NIXIE Torpedo Defense HK system with concentration on the development of the torpedo alertment and
 fire control / TWS integration into the NIXIE 25E tow.

 Research and development of new technologies and capabilities for torpedo defense initiated under the Future Naval Capabilities (FNC), Small Business and Innovative
 Research (SBIR), and/or other RDT&E initiatives are evaluated to determine their effectiveness and impact on improving ship survivability. Evaluations of new and
 emerging torpedo defense hardware and software in representative acoustic environments, against projected threats using both digital and hardware-in-the-loop
 simulations will be performed. The potential hardware and software will be used for integration into the modular and Commercial-Off-The-Shelf (COTS)-based design of
 AN/SLQ-25E, which allows for future capability growth into a NIXIE HK System to outpace the threat in torpedo defense.$$, $$Anti-Torpedo Torpedo Defensive System (ATTDS) is a system of systems, comprised of the TWS and the CAT planned to develop NIXIE HK new AN/SLQ-25
capabilities in order to pace the torpedo threat. This includes integrating and testing a kinematics-based target discrimination and fire control into the AN/SLQ-25E,
improving existing soft kill capabilities within AN/SLQ-25E, and adding a hard kill capability with a launcher for the MK 58 CRAW and the (ADC) MK5 and MK 2 Mod
6/8. The funds support the development of a torpedo alertment and fire control capability integrated into the AN/SLQ-25E tow system in support of a torpedo defense
requirements along with software improvements to specific NIXIE counter measures.

