A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
Anti-Torpedo Torpedo Defensive System (ATTDS) is a system of systems, comprised of the TWS and the CAT planned to develop NIXIE HK new AN/SLQ-25
capabilities in order to pace the torpedo threat. This includes integrating and testing a kinematics-based target discrimination and fire control into the AN/SLQ-25E,
improving existing soft kill capabilities within AN/SLQ-25E, and adding a hard kill capability with a launcher for the MK 58 CRAW and the (ADC) MK5 and MK 2 Mod
6/8. The funds support the development of a torpedo alertment and fire control capability integrated into the AN/SLQ-25E tow system in support of a torpedo defense
requirements along with software improvements to specific NIXIE counter measures.

