D. Acquisition Strategy
Torpedo Warning System (TWS) Program: ULTRA developed and produced five complete sensor sets. Pacific Engineering Incorporated (PEI) and In-Depth Engineering
INC. developed the stowage racks and fire control systems respectively. System integration supported fabrication and fielding of the five complete systems. Testing of
TWS SALVO software was complete and is currently in Fleet use. ULTRA continues to provide Fleet support for the system.

 AN/SLO-25E NIXIE Torpedo Hardkill Program will leverage the technologies developed in the TWS and CAT then incorporates them into the tow system and CRAW of
 the NIXIE 25E system. Development will also include improvements to the NIXIE winch to enable the integration of the TWS system, the design and development of a
 launching system that will launch the Compact Rapid Attack Weapon (CRAW) variant designed for torpedo defense. The launcher will be designed to have the capability
 to launch ADC-MK2 Acoustic countermeasure devices along with the CRAW. An incremental TI capability insertion approach will bring each new capability to the Fleet
 upon completion of the design and development phase of the capability.



