       Change Summary Explanation
       FUNDING CHANGES SINCE THE PREVIOUS PRESIDENT'S BUDGET AT THE OVERALL PE LEVEL:
       - FY 2025 decrease of $-0.076M is for incorporation of the Small Business Innovative Research (SBIR) transfer.
       - FY 2027 decrease of $-0.566M is for directed reductions to contractor support / contract services.

       SCHEDULE CHANGES SINCE THE PREVIOUS PRESIDENT'S BUDGET AT THE OVERALL PROJECT LEVEL:
       - Project 3216: CV-TSC Fleet Capability Release (FCR-6) 'Test and Cert' milestone has been expanded from 1Q25-2Q25 to 1Q25-3Q25 (+1 quarter) to
       incorporate an emergent requirement to develop/integrate/test a new interface with the MH-60S Knightlink. The MH-60S Knightlink interface distributes MH-60S
       Full Motion Video (FMV) to the Carrier Combat System (CS) for detection, classification, and localization of Surface Warfare (SUW) threats. Additional time was
       also required to account for the updated Carrier Combat System Integration Test (CSIT) schedule, which is a required event each CS element to achieve combat
       system certification. The cadence of future FCR schedules has been updated to account for increased software development, additional external interface testing,
       and the updated schedule of the Carrier CSIT.




