C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                   FY 2025     FY 2026       FY 2027
Title: ADCP Development                                                                                                                  86.301      75.711        71.312
Description: ADCP is an evolving, delivered and managed product distributed to customers ensuring the requisite tools
and services needed to seamlessly and securely build, deploy and sustain successful Command and Control (C2) mission
applications. Funding directly supports the design, development, testing and evaluation, engineering, and the product/program
management to build functionality and scalability of the AOC platform, hybrid cloud architecture, and underlying infrastructure. In
addition, it supports all accreditation and cybersecurity efforts required to obtain and maintain the AOC's authorities to operate
across multiple impact levels and platform and network infrastructures. To speed product development, funding supports
enablement services, data science, data engineering, data modeling/governance, and process automation. Funding also supports
network and platform architecture development and prototyping to increase platform, communications, and network efficiency
and capabilities. Lastly, funding supports continued development and fielding of Application Transformation (AppTX), integration
of Maven Smart Systems, and implementation of Information Technology Service Management (ITSM) tools, technologies, and
processes to ensure that ADCP services are delivered efficiently and effectively

FY 2026 Plans:
- Continue to support Continuous Integration and Continuous Delivery (CI/CD) pipelines operating in cloud-native environments
- Continue transition of containerized C2 applications to the production-ready open-source system

Operational Systems Development

C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                       FY 2025    FY 2026       FY 2027
- Continue to increase enhanced security observability tooling in support of application customers and platform services via a
Security Operations Center
- Continue iterative delivery of automation for monitoring and tracking services for application customer usage
- Continue to improve C2 mission application reliability and decrease lead time for new capability delivery
- Continue to optimize implementation of commercially managed platform and infrastructure services on available public cloud
service provider offerings and provide architectural/engineering support to ongoing managed platform operations
- Continue to develop, test, and deliver operationalized connected edge platform capabilities for AOC focused C2 applications
- Continue to align and support core DAF Battle Network (DBN) C2 application tenants including managing and optimizing the
C2IMERA and AppTx cloud environments, providing security monitoring to all AOC sites, and converging KR applications with
DAF Cloudworks
- Continue Identity, Credential, and Access Management (ICAM) development to support the Hardened Application Platform
(HAP) disconnected operations solution
- Continue supporting platform tenants with planning and architecture for developmental and operational testing of fielded
application capabilities
- Complete migration of applications to the preferred DAF BATTLE NETWORK platforms
- Supporting integration of AOC with DAF Battle Network (DBN) and Theater Air Planning System of Systems (TAP-SoS)
- Support cloud-hosted self-monitoring access for C2 mission application development teams to manage path to production
- Improve data management and sharing through iterative improvements to enterprise data governance
- Improve access and availability of unique internal-facing IT products and services to best enable program execution
- Support platform and infrastructure convergence with AOC WS modernized hardware and infrastructure at the edge supporting
contested, degraded, and operationally limited (CDOL) environments
FY 2027 Plans:
- Will continue to provide enhance security observability and remediation tools and services in support of application customers
and platform services via a Security Operations Center
- Will continue iterative delivery of automation for observability, monitoring, and tracking of services for application customer usage
- Will continue to improve C2 mission application reliability and decrease lead times for new capability delivery
- Will continue to optimize managed platform and infrastructure services on available public cloud service provider and provide
architectural/engineering support to ongoing managed platform operations across the AOC enterprise
- Will continue development, improvement, and delivery of operationalized connected edge platform capabilities through the AOC/
AppTX hybrid architecture model to deliver fight tonight capability with parity for remaining legacy on-premise and developing
cloud operations.
- Will continue to integrate with TAP-SoS and DAF Battle Network (DBN) C2 systems in support of Program Executive Office
C3BM mission threads

Operational Systems Development

C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                   FY 2025      FY 2026       FY 2027
- Will continue to support cloud-hosted self-monitoring access for C2 mission application development
- Will continue to improve AppTx and C2IMERA data management, tagging, and sharing through iterative improvements to
enterprise data governance
- Will continue supporting platform tenants with planning and architecture for developmental and operational testing of fielded
application capabilities by leveraging and improving AppTx capabilities
- Will continue to improve access and availability of unique internal-facing IT products and service to best enable program
execution in support of C2 application delivery to DAF Battle Network (DBN) weapon systems
- Will continue to integrate Maven Smart Systems Commercial Off The Shelf (COTS) licenses to provide AI-driven workflows and
data connections that enable high functioning cross-platform interoperability for the modern AOC, capabilities required for success
in Major Theater War and critical to out-pacing adversaries by replacing legacy systems
- Will begin supporting efforts to enhance data flow between C2 systems through improved network functionality
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
FY 2027 funding decreases due to discontinuing Platform as a Service (PaaS) to cloud connected edge environments and
discontinuing support of Continuous Integration and Continuous Delivery (CI/CD) pipelines.
