C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                   FY 2025     FY 2026       FY 2027
Title: ADCP Development                                                                                                                  86.301      75.711        71.312
Description: ADCP is an evolving, delivered and managed product distributed to customers ensuring the requisite tools
and services needed to seamlessly and securely build, deploy and sustain successful Command and Control (C2) mission
applications. Funding directly supports the design, development, testing and evaluation, engineering, and the product/program
management to build functionality and scalability of the AOC platform, hybrid cloud architecture, and underlying infrastructure. In
addition, it supports all accreditation and cybersecurity efforts required to obtain and maintain the AOC's authorities to operate
across multiple impact levels and platform and network infrastructures. To speed product development, funding supports
enablement services, data science, data engineering, data modeling/governance, and process automation. Funding also supports
network and platform architecture development and prototyping to increase platform, communications, and network efficiency
and capabilities. Lastly, funding supports continued development and fielding of Application Transformation (AppTX), integration
of Maven Smart Systems, and implementation of Information Technology Service Management (ITSM) tools, technologies, and
processes to ensure that ADCP services are delivered efficiently and effectively

FY 2026 Plans:
- Continue to support Continuous Integration and Continuous Delivery (CI/CD) pipelines operating in cloud-native environments
- Continue transition of containerized C2 applications to the production-ready open-source system


