A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
The COMPASS BRIGHT project develops Signals Intelligence (SIGINT) and Radio Frequency Measurement and Signature Intelligence (MASINT) capabilities for
transition to Department ISR systems. COMPASS BIGHT pursues SIGINT technologies for project transition, to include Communications Intelligence (COMINT),
Electronic Intelligence (ELINT), Audio, Analytics, and Special Signals of Interest. COMPASS BRIGHT will pursue multi-INT cross-cue and fusion capabilities from other
disciplines such as Geospatial Intelligence (GEOINT) in order to create a holistic ISR picture for the warfighter and the Intelligence Community (IC). COMPASS BRIGHT
projects are selected through an annual data call process whereby the SIGINT Capabilities Working Group (SCWG) evaluates proposals from the laboratories, systems,
and classified mission partners.

 The program office authority extends to accomplishment of out-of-cycle COMPASS BRIGHT efforts. These tasks may be filtered through the SCWG outside the normal
 vetting process to expedite acquisition of capabilities for the warfighter.

