C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                              FY 2025     FY 2026       FY 2027
Title: Air Traffic Control (ATC) Future Technologies (AFT)                                                                           6.829       7.184         5.927
Description: AFT is a multi-project investment portfolio focused on identifying and documenting capability gaps and
associated future technologies in multiple areas of aircraft launch and recovery for both fixed and expeditionary operations.
AFT works directly with Headquarters Air Force (HAF), Air Force Flight Standards Agency (AFFSA), Air Force Research
Laboratory (AFWERX), and industry to develop and refine airfield operations requirements by assessing tech evaluations and
demonstrations. AFT projects seek to enable Agile Combat Employment (ACE) operations in forward locations and addresses
obsolescence of current technology, identifies new required technology, and closes airfield operations capability gaps.

FY 2026 Plans:
- Continue Lightweight Deployable-Instrument Landing System (LD-ILS) localizer array proof-of-concept testing
for Small Footprint - Precision Approach Landing Capability (SF-PALC) efforts
- Begin mechanical packaging of the complete LD-ILS into a more compact, deployable end-item
- Start test and evaluation of flight inspection drones
- Complete operational assessment of Mobile Air Traffic System (MATS) software
FY 2027 Plans:
- Will continue mechanical packaging of the complete Lightweight Deployable Instrument Landing System (LD-ILS) into a more
compact, deployable end-item
- Will complete test and evaluation of flight inspection drones
- Will begin SF-PALC market research on both the non-traditional Tactical Transponder Landing System (TTLS) approaches and
the LD-ILS approach
- Will release RFP for SF-PALC material solution
- Will conduct down-select and conduct contract award for SF-PALC material solution
- Will begin requirements development for Man Portable Tactical Navigation (MP-TACAN) anti-jamming efforts
- Will begin study of requirements for a Mobile/Deployable ATC Tower in response to emerging requirements
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Decrease due to reprogramming for higher Department of War Priorities.
