Operational Systems Development
 2. The Multifunction Tactical Radar System (MTRS) will be capable of supporting Air Traffic Control (ATC) surveillance and communication, weather alerts, Unmanned
 Aircraft System (UAS) detection, and air battle management command control (BMC2) situational awareness. MTRS provides mobile ATC surveillance radar capability
 in an Agile Combat Operations (ACE) environment to replace the the unsupportable legacy (1970's-era) AN/MPN-14K. The last AN/MPN-14K will decommission in
 FY 2028. MTRS Initial Operational Capability (IOC) is anticipated in FY 2030. Two refurbished Air Traffic Control Navigation, Integration, and Coordination System
 (ATNAVICS) along with the three Africa Command (AFRICOM) Expeditionary Scalable MCRs will provide a limited material solution until MTRS IOC.

 3. The Tactical ATC Command and Control (C2) Operating Systems (TACOS) will automate, and display sensor feeds and includes the communication radios and voice
 switch needed by controllers to communicate to aircraft, host nations, and other agencies. TACOS will include the shelters, furniture, laptops, servers, software, power-
 supplies, and communications equipment needed for controllers to perform their mission in environments when existing infrastructure is damaged or does not exist.
 TACOS will include software interfaces with the greater Department of Air Force (DAF) Battle Network as well as appropriate C2 nodes for air battle management and
 counter-small UAS sensors and networks.

 This program element may include necessary civilian pay expenses required to manage, execute, and deliver weapon system capability. The use of such program funds
 would be in addition to the civilian pay expenses budgeted in program element 0605827F, 0605828F, 0605829F, 0605831F, 0605832F, 0605833F, 0605898F,
 0606398F.

 This program is in Budget Activity 7, Operational System Development because this budget activity includes development efforts to upgrade systems that have been
 fielded or have received approval for full rate production and anticipate production funding in the current or subsequent fiscal year.

