Title: Air Traffic Control (ATC) Future Technologies (AFT)                                                                           6.829       7.184         5.927
Description: AFT is a multi-project investment portfolio focused on identifying and documenting capability gaps and
associated future technologies in multiple areas of aircraft launch and recovery for both fixed and expeditionary operations.
AFT works directly with Headquarters Air Force (HAF), Air Force Flight Standards Agency (AFFSA), Air Force Research
Laboratory (AFWERX), and industry to develop and refine airfield operations requirements by assessing tech evaluations and
demonstrations. AFT projects seek to enable Agile Combat Employment (ACE) operations in forward locations and addresses
obsolescence of current technology, identifies new required technology, and closes airfield operations capability gaps.

