- Will continue mechanical packaging of the complete Lightweight Deployable Instrument Landing System (LD-ILS) into a more
compact, deployable end-item
- Will complete test and evaluation of flight inspection drones
- Will begin SF-PALC market research on both the non-traditional Tactical Transponder Landing System (TTLS) approaches and
the LD-ILS approach
- Will release RFP for SF-PALC material solution
- Will conduct down-select and conduct contract award for SF-PALC material solution
- Will begin requirements development for Man Portable Tactical Navigation (MP-TACAN) anti-jamming efforts
